articles.summary: The continuous claim in between Ripple and SEC has actually seen some brand-new advancements over the previous 24 hr. These extra orders are a problem for Ripple Labs, as they will trigger the fight to drag out even longer. Ad Magistrate Judge Sarah Netburn has actually provided 3 'text-only' orders in the Ripple case. The very first order gave the SEC's demand to extend the quick Discovery due date to August 31 and the specialist discovery due date to October 15.  The 2nd and 3rd orders given demands from Execs Garlinghouse and Chris Larsen on 6/2 and 6/11 that she release demand letters to foreign entities to acquire global discovery files.
articles.title: Ripple Gets a Setback in Lawsuit Against SEC
